Egypt has now been based for almost two years on a provisional, multiple amended text, which weakens institutional stability and leads to legal confusion.
This new initiative has only provided for an even greater division of the country.
For his opponents, the president persists in his "autocratic delirium" by continuing to "break his word" and "step right with feet".
On the part of its supporters, it is assured that it is a way to end the institutional and political crisis as soon as possible and to speed up the transition process.
A referendum should be held within 14 days.
A very short period of time, which forces the brothers to refrain from their project to explain the text for section to the Egyptians.
For the President, it is also a way of reinventing his public and democratic legitimacy while protesting throughout the country.
After confirming in an interview with the American Week Show Time, Muhammad Mursi seems convinced that the Egyptians will vote in favour.
In particular, the Egyptian people, with this reluctance to an over-voicing vote, will be put to an ultimatum: "Either vote for my draft or I hold the unlimited authority", the latter, after the adoption of the Constitution, is supposed to end.
85 mostly Islamist members of this constitutional assembly adopted the text yesterday in a strange atmosphere.
The majority of the Liberals have failed to comply with the call.
Shortly before the Constitutional Declaration in mid-November, they turned away because they felt that they were unable to apply their views.
Representatives of human rights organizations, religious minorities or civil society have acted equally.
In order to achieve the decision-making capacity, 11 persons were added in every hurry yesterday morning, deputy members.
Some are very close to the Muslim brothers.
It is not surprising that the articles were mostly adopted unanimously.
The commentators found it entertaining, by the way, that the only difference of opinion of the day... came to the fore during the time of prayer, as some members of the body believed that the pendulum clock of the constitutional assembly was not accurate.
