In Akko you can visit the museum at Bad Al Basha, which houses several rooms of old Turkish baths with sculptures of the time visitors and bathing servants.
In Caesarea you should visit the unique private Ralli Museum, where you can admire sculptures by Dali and Rodin.
There are neither museum leaders nor souvenir shops.
Admission is free and donations are generally rejected.
