Šimon Ornest: At our concerts we want to collect positive energy
What do you think about taking place in less than a month of the world's downfall?
This is one of those disaster reports that we people so much like to jump to.
With our band The Tap Tap, we make fun of it and say that we are the only band in the world that can collect enough positive energy to stop or prevent the decline of the world.
In December, you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the world's downfall.
Can you introduce the project to our readers?
This is a national benefit event that we have been planning for two years.
For this purpose, we want to use the marketing potential of the Maya calendar, which is forecasted at 11:10 a.m. by the end of December 21.
On the day before that, i.e. December 20, three concerts will take place at the same time as 21:00 in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
The end of the concerts is expected to be about at the time that ends on the Pacific Island of Kiribati, which is in a time zone around 12 hours ahead of us, the Maya calendar ends.
Who made this idea?
Originally from me, we developed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
Not only do we want to collect enough positive energy to prevent the decline of the world, but we also want to reflect together with the public on the state in which we hand over this world to our children once.
At the end of the Maya calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, T-shirts, bags and key pendants against the world's downfall, with which people can also support us through www.e-tap.cz.
Together with other performers, the band The Tap Tap has also recorded the so-called anthem against the world's downfall with the title "World Falls Out".
Already today the anthem on YouTube is very popular. Will it also sound on the benefit concerts?
Of course, quite the end, provided that everything works and does not take place at the end of the world...
The anthem is to be sung at the same time by all performers at all three concerts.
In addition, the anthems are transmitted live in a direct circuit from Czech television.
The text of the hymn comes from Tomáš Hanák, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, also sings Xindl X with...
How did you get to the cooperation with both of them?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, which is related to the fact that we realize many benefit events and concerts...
We are trying to involve these people intensively in our projects.
It has been shown that most of them are interested in working with us and have fun at it.
What is the purpose of the proceeds of the concerts against the decline in the world?
For the establishment of the accessibility education centre Studeo, which we have been working with the association Tap at the Jedlička Institute for six years.
The students of the Jedlička Institute are regularly cared for by teachers who help them with different leisure activities.
Since the students themselves do not have the means to visit the teachers, we would like to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedlička Institute, an own building is to be created in which we then move into this project.
Several groups and performers perform at each concert.
Which criteria did you choose?
We wanted to create a program that addresses all generations, including children.
In Prague, for example, Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý perform.
