There are only a few really unique things, and I dare to claim that Tap Tap belongs to them.
Of course, the first impression that the viewer usually has is pity; this is only natural...
But this pity is absolutely unnecessary because people with disabilities are not lonely and abandoned beings that we should regret.
It is people who are able to live and develop a full life if they have the necessary means.
I always say that if people with disabilities succeed in something, this is not only progress for them themselves, but for the whole society.
